HEADWORD: Presbyterianism
<hw>Pres`by*te"ri*an*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>presbyt⟦eacute⟧rianisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>That form of church
government which invests presbyters with all spiritual power, and admits
no prelates over them; also, the faith and polity of the Presbyterian
churches, taken collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presbyterium</ent>⟦br⟧
